{{Infobox journal | italic title = force | title = Development Policy Review | cover = | editor = | discipline = Planning and Development | former_names = | abbreviation = Dev. Policy Rev. | publisher = [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the [[Overseas Development Institute]]. | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1966-Present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.522 | impact-year = 2011 | website = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1467-7679| link1 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1467-7679/issues | link1-name = Online access | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0950-6764 | eISSN = 1467-7679 }} '''''Development Policy Review''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by [[Wiley-Blackwell]] 6 times a year on behalf of the [[Overseas Development Institute]] (ODI). The journal was established in 1966 and focuses on the links between research and policy in international development, addressing contemporary questions from a range of disciplines across the social sciences.
