{{Infobox book | name = General Relativity | title_orig = | translator = | image = General Relativity (book).jpg | caption = Hardcover edition | author = [[Robert Wald]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States of America | language = [[English language|English]] | series = | subject = [[Physics]] | genre = Non-fiction | publisher = [[The University of Chicago Press]] | pub_date = 1984 | media_type = Print | pages = 491 | isbn = 0-226-87033-2 | dewey= 530.1/1 19 | congress= QC173.6 .W35 1984 | oclc= 10018614 | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''General Relativity''' is a popular textbook on [[Einstein]]'s theory of [[general relativity]] written by [[Robert Wald]].<ref>{{cite web|title=General Relativity|url=http://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/G/bo5952261.html|website=[[University of Chicago Press]]|publisher=press.uchicago.edu|accessdate=22 February 2017}}</ref>
==Background== It was published by the University of Chicago in 1984. The book, a tome of almost 500 pages, covers many aspects of the General Theory of Relativity. It is divided into two parts, the second of which covers more advanced topics such as causal structure, spinors and quantum effects. The book uses the [[Abstract index notation]] for [[tensors]].
