'''Ricardo Cirera Salse''' (Os de Balaguer, 1864-Barcelona, August 1932) was a geomagnetist who conducted the first geomagnetic survey of the Philippines and who founded the [[El Ebro Observatory]] in [[Roquetes, Tarragona|Roquetes]] (1904), [[Catalonia]], [[Spain]].  He was also involved in the founding of the scientific journal [[Ibérica (journal)|Ibérica]].

